    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Romans",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 6,
        "summary": "Baptism is in similitude of the death, burial, and resurrection of Christ\u2014The wages of sin is death\u2014Christ brings eternal life.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that grace may abound?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 20:32 (29\u201334).",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "God forbid. How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0May it not be!",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 2:41.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Know ye not, that so many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 27:25.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p3",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death: that like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Immersion.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Death of.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 159
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for; Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 170
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if we have been planted together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also in the likeness of his resurrection:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Types of, in Memory.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 2:20; 3:3; 2\u00a0Tim. 2:11.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Resurrection.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should not serve sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 4:22 (22\u201324); Col. 3:9.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 2:11.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0brought to an end, freed.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 10:32 (32\u201333).",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For he that is dead is freed from sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 6:7 \u2026 dead to sin\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0acquitted, cleared.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now if we be dead with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Death of.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing that Christ being raised from the dead dieth no more; death hath no more dominion over him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Resurrection.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For in that he died, he died unto sin once: but in that he liveth, he liveth unto God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 9:28.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 7:27; 10:10.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Likewise reckon ye also yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 2:19.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let not sin therefore reign in your mortal body, that ye should obey it in the lusts thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mortality.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither yield ye your members as instruments of unrighteousness unto sin: but yield yourselves unto God, as those that are alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness unto God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 4:27 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:5.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0weapons.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:19; Hel. 3:35.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 179,
                        "end": 192
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For sin shall not have dominion over you: for ye are not under the law, but under grace.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Rom. 6:14 For in so doing sin\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 2:29 (26\u201329).",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? God forbid.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0May it not be!",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1424
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Know ye not, that to whom ye yield yourselves servants to obey, his servants ye are to whom ye obey; whether of sin unto death, or of obedience unto righteousness?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:34.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 3:27 (26\u201327); 34:34 (33\u201336); Hel. 14:31 (29\u201331). TG\u00a0Obedience.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But God be thanked, that ye were the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 5:8 (7\u20138). TG\u00a0Remission of Sins.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual; Sin.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I speak after the manner of men because of the infirmity of your flesh: for as ye have yielded your members servants to uncleanness and to iniquity unto iniquity; even so now yield your members servants to righteousness unto holiness.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For when ye were the servants of sin, ye were free from righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0unrestricted by.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "What fruit had ye then in those things whereof ye are now ashamed? for the end of those things is death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0benefit, reward.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now being made free from sin, and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness, and the end everlasting life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 8:2 (1\u20134); Rev. 2:17 (17, 26).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0benefit, reward.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sanctification.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wages.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Death; Death, Spiritual, First.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eternal Life.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}